headline: HP warns of profit impact from Trump's China tariffs. Stock slips.
summary: While releasing an earnings and revenue beat in its fiscal first quarter, HP Inc. (HPQ) expects President Trump's tariff policies around China to weigh on the computer company's profit outlook for the second quarter and full-year 2025. Catch Yahoo Finance's full interview with HP CEO Enrique Lores following the earnings release on Thursday. Simultaneously, Dell Technologies (DELL) also beat its fourth quarter earnings estimates, while falling short on guidance. Morning Brief anchors Brad Smith and Madison Mills report further on the latest earnings prints from the two tech names. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief here. This post was written by Luke Carberry Mogan.

headline: HP Stock Drops After PC Maker Gives Weak Outlook, Steps Up Layoffs
summary: HP stock fell, after the computer company said earnings would fall short of Wall Street estimates this quarter, and outlined plans to cut up to 2,000 more jobs.  Late Thursday, HP reported higher quarterly revenue and lower profit, while adjusted earnings missed analysts' expectations.  Adjusted earnings were 74 cents a share, just below the 75 cents expected by analysts surveyed by FactSet.

headline: Why It’s Too Late to Tap Into the PayPal (PYPL) Stock Rally
summary: Payments pioneer PayPal Holdings (PYPL) was in rally mode for most of 2024, delivering both price and value for its patient yet loyal shareholders.
